description: The `Rcs` table stores Radio Communication Settings (RCS) parameters for specific cells, including inactivity timers, release delays, and emergency mode settings, at a particular point in time.  dateTime: Timestamp of the recorded data; Area_Name: Geographic area of the cell; CellId: Unique identifier of the cell; Id2: Redundant cell identifier; Id3:  Unclear identifier (likely a constant in this sample); vsDataType: Data type identifier; vsDataFormatVersion: Version of data format; Rcs.tInactivityTimerBr: BR inactivity timer; Rcs.tNasInactivityTimer: NAS inactivity timer; Rcs.raiReleaseDelayTimerBr: RAI release delay timer; Rcs.rcsId: RCS ID; Rcs.tInactivityTimer: Inactivity timer; Rcs.extendInactEmergency: Emergency inactivity timer extension; Rcs.bufferInactivityTimerBr: Buffer inactivity timer; Rcs.rlcDlDeliveryFailureAction: Action on RLC DL delivery failure; Rcs.extendInactAfterVolteRel: Inactivity timer extension after VoLTE release; Rcs.extendInactEmMode: Emergency mode inactivity timer setting.
